sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Main as Electron main process
    participant Home as Desktop data preparation
    participant Window as BrowserWindow / Electron session
    participant Supervisor as DaemonSupervisor
    participant Daemon as Selected workbench daemon
    participant App as workbench-app renderer

    User->>Main: Launch Nerve desktop
    Main->>Main: Acquire single-instance lock
    alt Another instance already owns the lock
        Main-->>User: Focus existing instance and quit this launch
    else Lock acquired
        Main->>Home: Prepare active data directory
        alt Unversioned legacy local NERVE_HOME
            Home-->>User: Ask before replacing legacy home
            alt User accepts migration
                Home->>Home: Rename complete home to timestamped backup
                Home->>Home: Initialize current store and restore readable auth only
            else User declines
                Home-->>Main: Quit without changing the home
            end
        end
        Main->>Main: Configure loopback proxy bypass and tray
        Main->>Window: Create window and show loading page
        Main->>Supervisor: ensureDaemon(options)

        alt Remote mode
            Supervisor->>Daemon: Normalize URL and health-check with token
            Note over Supervisor,Daemon: Monitor only, owned = false
        else Healthy local daemon already exists
            Supervisor->>Daemon: Read daemon metadata and health-check
            Note over Supervisor,Daemon: Reuse and monitor, owned = false
        else No healthy local daemon
            Supervisor->>Daemon: Spawn workbench-server child
            Daemon->>Daemon: Initialize file-first storage, runtime, auth, and listeners
            Daemon-->>Supervisor: Ready metadata (URL, token, capabilities)
            Note over Supervisor,Daemon: Supervise child and restart with backoff, owned = true
        end

        Supervisor-->>Main: ManagedDaemon
        Main->>Window: Install HttpOnly nerve_token cookie
        Main->>Daemon: Fetch desktop settings with Bearer token
        Daemon-->>Main: close-to-tray and desktop settings
        Main->>Window: Clear service worker/cache storage for daemon origin
        Main->>Window: loadURL(daemon URL)
        Window->>Daemon: GET application route
        Daemon-->>Window: Bundled workbench-app HTML / JS / CSS
        Window->>App: Start Svelte application
        App->>Daemon: Authenticated REST requests
        App->>Daemon: Open Protocol v1 WebSocket (local stream)
        Daemon-->>App: Welcome, recovery snapshot/replay, then live events

        loop Health monitoring
            Supervisor->>Daemon: Health check
            alt Owned daemon crashes or remains unhealthy
                Supervisor->>Daemon: Restart child with bounded backoff
                Supervisor-->>Main: restarting / ready status
                Main-->>Window: Update overlay and tray state
            else Existing or remote daemon is unhealthy
                Supervisor-->>Main: Report status only, never spawn or stop it
            end
        end

        User->>Main: Quit
        Main-->>App: Notify quit started
        alt Selected daemon is owned
            Main->>Supervisor: stop()
            Supervisor->>Daemon: Graceful child shutdown
            Daemon-->>Supervisor: Stopped
            Main->>Main: Retry Electron quit
        else Existing local or remote daemon
            Note over Main,Daemon: Leave unowned daemon running
        end
        Main-->>User: Desktop exits
    end
